                        about_title: [{
                            type: a,
                            text: "Out with the Old, in with the New: Understanding a Strange New Species",
                            spans: []
                        }],
                        about_text: [{
                            type: c,
                            text: "The internet was once 4 people. Not everyone was free to create and publish. Then, digital creation became a specialized skill that only a handful were capable of. Today, the doors have been blown wide open. Anyone can create and scale amazing digital products - and it all comes down to one very important catalyst. ",
                            spans: []
                        }, {
                            type: c,
                            text: o,
                            spans: []
                        }, {
                            type: c,
                            text: "In this talk, Erwin Luijendijk and Ilja van Eck discuss the role of no-code in changing the landscape of digital creation for good. From the history of web development, to the birth of the new species of creator, they’re here to bring you a whole new perspective on the role of no-code in transforming the wild, wild web. Oh, and not to mention how it’s forever changed the ‘it’s complicated’ relationship between developers and designers. Join them to hear more about how you too can save time, protect sanity, unlock speed, and push the boundaries of design with tools that just hit different. ",
                            spans: []
                        }]
